title: For Sale:  NAA Mini Revolver 22mag/22lr
postcontent:
180 cash, firm. Transfer to be done at a FFL Dealer, buyer assumes fee.

This is a 1 5/8 inch barrel, is 5 3/8 inches in overall length, and weighs 6.2 ounces. It comes with both the 22 Magnum Cylinder and the 22 Long Rifle convertible cylinder. It also comes with a Sherpa lined gun rug and a in the waistband holster. You also get all of my 22 magnum rounds ( a bunch of cci hps and 8 cci shot shells) and I'll throw in a couple hundred Long Rifle rounds.

NAA mini-revolvers are made in the USA of stainless steel with a nicely polished matte finish. All are single action (SA) revolvers with spur triggers. The cylinders hold 5 cartridges, and there are safety notches between the chambers into which the nose of the hammer (which is also the firing pin) can be lowered to allow safe carry with the cylinder fully loaded. The grip frames are of the "bird's head" type and most models come with attractive laminated wood grips. The sights on most models are rudimentary, consisting of a rounded front blade and the raised rear edge of the frame.

NAA mini-revolvers are so tiny that they are cute, but they are not toys. They are precisely made and very functional deep concealment pistols. And a mini-revolver can be concealed in the vest pocket of a three piece suit. To me it is the minimum satisfactory concealed carry handgun.

title: For Sale:  Finn or Finnish Mosin M28/30
postcontent:
What we have here is a somewhat unusual 1939 dated Finnish Mosin M28/30 rifle with matching bolt.

It was originally made for The Finnish Civil Guard and was later transferred to the Finnish Army.

It's in a great looking two tone stock (with lots of honest handeling marks but no splits or cracks, at one point the butt portion was on an M91 or M28(as evidenced by the (SYT) mark in the fingergroove), it was later "Finn" spliced to an artic birch forend as can be seen in the pic.s.

It also has the unusual 2 marking that is said to denote bore condition, however it is also prominent on a lot of later made M39's in the 212,000 serial range.

Bluing is a nice arsenal refurbished condition and the crown is nice and tight with no counter-bore however there are some rough spots in barrel as these were often fired with corrosive ammo.

It has the correct HV (jamb free) marked magazine and aluminum barrel sleeve that was added for accuracy.

All in all a nice collectable Finnish 28/30 that you don't have to bid on or pay shipping charges for.  

The sling and sling hangers/swivels are not part of the sale.

Selling this one and a few others to fund another Mosin variant purchase.

$400 FTF (face to face) sale in the Richmond, Mechanicsville, Henrico area.

title: For Sale/Trade:  270 Winchester SM
postcontent:
The 270 WSM is a new centerfire rifle cartridge developed in partnership with Browning Arms Company and Winchester ammunition, making its debut and introduced to the shooting public in 2001.

 The 270 WSM is a commercial cartridge based on the 404 jeffery cartridge case, shortening to 2.100" and necking down to .27 caliber and sharpening the shoulder angle to 35 degrees the new 270 WSM cartridge has plenty of case capacity.

 The 270 WSM cartridge achieves its useful purpose as an excellent cartridge for white-tailed deer, mule deer, sheep, elk, moose and bears, 27 caliber is a time proven caliber for deer size animals.

 The 270 WSM cartridge is a well thought out cartridge as Winchester is no stranger in 27 caliber cartridge development. Winchester has now developed 2 cartridges in this caliber; 

 (270 Winchester in 1923), and 
 (270 Winchester Short Magnum in 2001).

 The 270 WSM factory loadings show a velocity of 3,275 feet per second for a 130 grain bullet for deer hunting and this translates to moderate recoil for the shooter with plenty of bullet energy at the 500 yard mark to flatten a white-tailed deer size animal. The 140 grain bullet serves the elk hunter well all the way out to 400 yards and the 150 grain bullet will certainly handle moose size animals all the way out to 300 yards.

 The 270 WSM cartridge, chambered in a short actioned light weight rifle may well be the ultimate combination for a superb mountain rifle in rugged terrain.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Pre-64 Winchester 94
postcontent:
I got this Pre-64 Winchester 94 a while back as a welcome home gift from Afghanistan. 



Even though I'm not a lever action guy,  I kept it with the intent to restore it. For a variety of reasons (the biggest of which is that I'm just not a lever action fan) I never got around to doing anything to it. I did find a replacement top-eject .30-30 barrel for it; there's nothing wrong with the original barrel on it, other than it's in .32 Special (not a problem in itself, but again I'm not a lever action fan; sorry, all my childhood heroes used the M-1 Garand or bolt actions). This would be a great project gun for anyone who is into these old west/cowboy types of weapons. 



The serial number indicates that it was built in 1941. It is mechanically sound (verified by a local gunsmith) although it has a lot of finish wear on the receiver (I understand that this was pretty common with the Winnie 94's). The wood is a little worn in some spots, but seems to be pretty good overall; there are no cracks or splits in it that I can see. There is considerably less bluing worn off the barrel.





What can I say, it's a 71 year old gun. It's older and it was used, but it was also taken care of. 

I'm assigning a trade value of $600 to this. I'm not trying to overestimate it's worth, but they also don't make these anymore.

Trade interests: 

-S&W model 15 with a 4" heavy barrel .38 Special.

-Bare bones Remington 700, caliber doesn't matter as long as I can rebarrel it to .308.

-Glock 20.

-What else do you have? Try me, the worst I'll say is "No thanks".

This trade will be FTF in NC for now. It's the holidays, and with all the lunacy currently going on, I ain't even gonna think about shipping....
